  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN157.1-kilavi">pirivuṇarttiya tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What SHE said to the confidante who informed [her] about the separation.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN157.1">
              <l>ariyaṟ peṇṭi ṉalkuṟ koṇṭa</l>
              <l>pakuvāyp pāḷaik kuvimulai curanta</l>
              <l>vari<supplied>ni</supplied>ṟak kaluḻi yāra māntic</l>
              <l>ceruvēṭṭuc cilaikkuñ ceṅka ṇāṭavar</l>
              <l>villiṭa vīḻntōr patukkaik kōṅki</l>
              <l>ṉelli malarnta paiṅkoṭi yatiral</l>
              <l>perumpular vaikaṟai yarumpoṭu vāṅkik</l>
              <l>kāṉa yāṉai kavaḷaṅ koḷḷu</l>
              <l>mañcuvaru neṟiyiṭait ta<supplied>mi</supplied>yar ceṉmār</l>
              <l>neñcuṇa moḻi<supplied>pa ma</supplied>ṉṉē tōḻi</l>
              <l>muṉaipulam peyartta pulleṉ maṉṟattup</l>
              <l>peyaluḻa nekiḻntu veyiluṟac cāay</l>
              <l>vi<supplied>ṉai</supplied>yaḻi pāvaiyi ṉulaṟi</l>
              <l>maṉaiyoḻin tiru<supplied>t</supplied>tal vallu vōrkkē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>They speak indeed, friend, so that [my] heart is in my mouth, (10)</l>
                <l>about him going alone on the frightening path, (9)</l>
                <l>where the forest elephant takes a mouthful (8)</l>
                <l>dragging, at great dawning dawn, along with the buds (7)</l>
                <l>the wild jasmine in fresh creepers that blossomed at night (6)</l>
                <l>by the cameg at the stone heap for those who fell when red-eyed</l>
                <l>men set [their] bows [at them, men] who roar when seeking a fight (4f.)</l>
                <l>after drinking [their] fill of the filtered, colourful muddy liquid (3)</l>
                <l>that is given in abundance by the round breast [made from] spathes with a split mouth (2)</l>
                <l>held on [their] hips by the toddy women, (1)</l>
                <l>– to one who is [just] capable of sitting [still], staying behind in the house, (14)</l>
                <l>shrivelled like a doll devoid of action, (13)</l>
                <l>emaciated when feeling the sunlight, unravelling when bearing the rain (12)</l>
                <l>on the empty village common from which [people] had to migrate to the frontier. (11)</l>
                
            <lg type="alternate" sameAs="9f">
                <l>He speaks indeed, friend, so that [my] heart is consumed, in order to go alone… (9f)</l></lg>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
